Information System: The WWW is a system of interconnected hypertext documents (web pages) that are accessed via the Internet. 


Hypertext: The WWW uses hypertext transfer protocol (HTTP) to link documents together, allowing users to navigate between them using hyperlinks. 


Software Layer: The WWW is considered a software layer built on top of the Internet. 


